    <li>
      <article class="update">
        <timeline-element>
          <time>February 04, 2021</time>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <h2><a href="/updates/2021/02/04/hello-openapi-webhooks/">Hello, OpenAPI webhooks</a></h2>
            <div class="tag-list">
                <a class="label" data-label-status="inverted">New</a>
            </div>
            <p><img src="/images/updates/openapi-webhooks.png" alt="openapi-webhooks.png" /></p>

<p><a href="https://github.com/OAI/OpenAPI-Specification/blob/master/versions/3.1.0.md">OpenAPI 3.1</a> has been released today. Some important changes are coming with this new version. Above all, the greatest improvement is the support of <code class="highlighter-rouge">webhooks</code>, at the same first level than <code class="highlighter-rouge">paths</code>.</p>

<p>We are glad to announce today that webhooks are now supported by Bump, as you can see in this <a href="https://bump.sh/doc/webhook-example">live example</a>.</p>

<p>We hope you‚Äôll enjoy this new feature, don‚Äôt hesitate to have a look to our <a href="https://docs.bump.sh/help/specifications-support/openapi-support/webhooks/">technical documentation</a> if necessary.</p>

          </div>
        </timeline-element>
      </article>
    </li>
    <li>
      <article class="update">
        <timeline-element>
          <time>January 10, 2021</time>
          <div class="timeline-content">
            <h2><a href="/updates/2021/01/10/customize-operation-url/">Customize operation URL</a></h2>
            <div class="tag-list">
                <a class="label" data-label-status="inverted">Improvement</a>
            </div>
            <p>OpenAPI provides field <code class="highlighter-rouge">servers</code> on OperationObject, as an alternative url to service an operation.</p>
<blockquote>
  <p>If an alternative server object is specified at the Path Item Object or Root level, it will be overridden by this value. cf <a href="https://github.com/OAI/OpenAPI-Specification/blob/master/versions/3.0.0.md#operationObject">OpenAPI-Specification</a></p>
</blockquote>

<p>From now on, Operations <code class="highlighter-rouge">servers</code> are supported to customize your operations examples (in definition and curl example).</p>

          </div>
        </timeline-element>
      </article>
